<HEAD>Unemployed Carpenter Claims World Record For Television Watching</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 24-year-old unemployed carpenter claimed a world record for continuous television watching today after spending 168 hours gazing at the small screen. `` Most of the shows were pretty good. In fact, I could have gone on for days and days,'' said <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Woods </PERSON>, who completed his record attempt in a box 20 yards above one of <LOCATION> Sydney </LOCATION>'s busiest thoroughfares. The <LOCATION> Sydney </LOCATION> man said a masseur and an electric nerve stimulator helped him keep alert during the marathon stint. <PERSON> Woods </PERSON>, who was filmed by an Australian television show that concentrates of wierd and wacky achievements, said after the weeklong marathon effort that television programs `` really are n't that bad. The Guinness Book of Records does not list a current record for television watching.
