<FIRST>r w PM-StateTaxes     07-25 0526</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-State Taxes,490</SECOND>
<HEAD>More States Lowered Taxes Than Increased Them in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 More states decreased taxes than raised them this year, and the total increase among the 27 states was an unusually low $ 600 million, according to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Legislatures </ORGANIZATION>. The organization, in a survey of state tax policies, said 13 states raised taxes and 14 lowered them, with most revisions relatively minor. Traditionally, a tax change is considered `` large'' only if it results in at least a 5 percent increase or decrease in revenue. By this standard, the only `` large'' increases this year were reported in <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>, and the only `` large'' decreases came in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dakota </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>, according to the conference. The survey is part of a broader report to be released this week at the conference's annual meeting in <LOCATION> Reno </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nev. </LOCATION> `` To a considerable extent, 1988 tax actions are related to the tax policy followed last year,'' the conference said. `` The large number of tax increases last year helped to improve financial conditions and thereby avoided the need to increase taxes this year.'' The organization also said the $ 600 million tax increase this year is smaller than those in most recent years. In 1985, the survey said, there was a tax reduction of $ 1.3 billion. All other years since 1981 had tax increases of at least $ 1.1 billion, which came in 1986. The next smallest increase in this decade was a $ 2.3 billion rise in 1984. State tax collections exceed $ 260 billion per year, according to the conference. The survey said income taxes were reduced in 10 states and increased in two; motor fuel taxes were hiked in nine states; and sales taxes _ either through a higher rate or broader base _ went up in five states while being lowered in three others. The most significant tax increases this year came in <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, although they were spared major tax hikes in 1987. Citizens in <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dakota </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION> saw the biggest tax reductions after seeing taxes increase in 1987. <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> were the only two states to increase income taxes. <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> also hiked a number of other taxes including property and motor fuel taxes. <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> were the only states to increase their sales taxes significantly. <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>'s sales tax went up 2 cents on food, utilities and drugs; and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>'s rate jumped 1 cent for a 13-month period. While the most frequent tax changes involved motor fuel, sales or income taxes, some states found other sources of revenue. <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> increased their cigarette tax, joining 11 states that did the same in 1987, and <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> for the first time imposed such a tax. A recent trend of taxing mail order sales continued this year, with <LOCATION> Tennessee </LOCATION> joining 11 other states in enacting such a tax, which still faces court tests. <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> and parts of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> state increased taxes on hotel-motel rooms. <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> also increased its tax on hazardous waste while lowering a tax on aluminum casting. The property transfer tax increased in <LOCATION> Vermont </LOCATION> and insurance premium taxes were lowered in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
