<BYLINE>By RICK HAMPSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ARMAGH, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Assailants shot and killed a <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION> member of the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION>'s political wing today as Cardinal <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, delivering a sermon a mile away, denounced Americans who `` romanticize violence'' in <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Brendan </PERSON> <PERSON> Davidson </PERSON>, 33, was shot in the head as he answered a knock at his door from three men who apparently were dressed as policemen, police said. <PERSON> Davidson </PERSON> belonged to <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION>, the legal political wing of the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>, and was wounded in an assassination attempt last year. <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION> blamed <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> extremists for his killing. On Saturday, an <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> bomb killed a <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> couple and their 6-year-old son as they were driving just north of the <LOCATION> Ireland-Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> border. The mostly <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION>, fighting to drive <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> out of <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> and unite the island, has accepted responsibility, saying it attacked the wrong car. Press reports say the intended victim was a <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> judge. <PERSON> Davidson </PERSON> was shot at his home on Friendly Street as <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON>, leading a American peace pilgrims on a tour of <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, was attending Mass with 400 congregants at <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZAT