> could use its catamaran, but ordered both sides to proceed with the competition and bring any complaints to court when the race was over. `` The Cup has always involved sailing challenges between similar boats, but the judge has ordered us to sail, and we are ready to sail mismatch or not,'' said <PERSON> Mercury </PERSON> <PERSON> Bay </PERSON>'s <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Debreceny </PERSON>, <PERSON> Debrency </PERSON>, reached in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION>. `` If it's a mismatch, it will destroy the future of the <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Cup.'' <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, a spokesman for the Sail <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> group which is sponsoring the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION> entry, called the decision a victory for the American defenders and said his group is ready to race. `` Let's get the boats in the water and sail,'' <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> said. According to the judge, the <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Cup 1887 Deed of Gift, which established the rules for the sailing competition, is not specific about many of the changes in yacht racing since the first <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Cup in 1851. The <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yacht </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> held the Cup for more than 125 years until it lost in 1983 at <LOCATION> Newport </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> R.I. </LOCATION>, to the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Perth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yacht </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Stars </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Stripes _ the <ORGANIZATION> San </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Diego </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yacht </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION>'s entry _ recaptured it last year when it beat <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION> in the semifinals then beat the Austrlian yacht <PERSON> Kookaburra </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Perth </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>.
