<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Men dressed as policemen killed an <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> man Monday while Cardinal <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> delivered a sermon a mile away in which he implored Americans not to romanticize Irish violence. <PERSON> Brendan </PERSON> <PERSON> Davidson </PERSON>, a member of <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION>, the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>'s legal political wing, was shot in the head after answering a knock on his door, police said. <PERSON> Davidson </PERSON>, 33, belonged to the <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION>, the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>'s legal political wing. An <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> statement issued in <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION> said he was one of its members.
