<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     07-25 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stock Prices Steady After Sharp Falls</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices fell Monday amid bargain-hunting in light trading. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 9.5 points, or 0.5 percent, at 1,835.3 at midday, after having fallen 18 points in early trading. Volume was 169.1 million shares, compared to 233.1 million shares at the same time Friday. The early declines came on the back of a strong pound and poor performances in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> on Friday and in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> earlier Monday. Some traders said they were encouraged that the market found the energy to recover some ground. `` It has n't been all that bad,'' said one trader. The lows created `` a good buying opportunity'' in some stocks, he said. But the buying enthusiasm which lifted stocks was n't expected to carry into the afternoon, traders said. They said they expected the market to drift. `` I do n't think there's any great excitement,'' a trader said.
</TEXT>
