<HEAD>Never Too Old To Collect Toy Cars</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Toy Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 When he was about 12 years old, <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON> figured he was too old to play with toy cars. When he turned 28, he realized maybe he was n't. The 38-year-old <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON> is one of about 6,000 members worldwide of Matchbox toy car collectors groups. The members trade, buy and sell the small-scale replicas of vehicles ranging from the <ORGANIZATION> Ferrari </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Testarossa </ORGANIZATION> to a <ORGANIZATION> Caterpillar </ORGANIZATION> earth mover. `` If you do it right, you can probably accumulate a little bit of wealth,'' said <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON>, a high school teacher. `` My mom and my wife are working for me at rummage sales. I have a network of people working for me,'' he said. <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON> figures the most valuable piece in the 700-vehicle collection is worth about $ 50. `` I'd categorize -LRB- the collection -RRB- in the infant stages based on what I've seen at the shows,'' he said. The smallest Matchbox cars sell for about $ 1.10 in hobby stores. Each year, <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON> says he acquires <ORGANIZATION> Matchbox </ORGANIZATION>'s new line of cars, usually about 12, and a few older models missing from his collection. <PERSON> Gibbons </PERSON> is a member of the <ORGANIZATION> Matchbox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Collectors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Waterloo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ontario </LOCATION>. The 900 club members receive the organization magazine every two months and meet annually. `` You get all types. They come from all walks of life,'' said <PERSON> Rita </PERSON> <PERSON> Schneider </PERSON>, membership secretary. `` A lot of the gentlemen are older and maybe they remember -LRB- the cars -RRB- from childhood.'' The other <LOCATIO