<HEAD>McDonald and Quality Inns at Odds Over McSleep</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Also on general news wires.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By DENISE LAYFIELD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Representatives of fast-food giant <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> testified Monday that <ORGANIZATION> Quality </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> was infringing upon its trademarks by using the name McSleep Inn for a new chain of economy hotels McDonald's took immediate exception last September to the use of the `` Mc'' prefix after Quality Inns announced the new chain of hotels, which will offer a night's lodging for $ 20 to $ 29. After repeated warnings from McDonald's to stop using the name, Quality Inns filed suit against the international hamburger chain, asking a federal judge to declare that <PERSON> McSleep </PERSON> does not infringe on the chain's trademarks. McDonald's counter-sued Quality Inns, charging that use of the `` Mc'' prefix constitutes an infringement and that the public will likely confuse the inns with <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>. `` We wanted to remove any cloud that was hanging over Quality,'' said <PERSON> Laurence </PERSON> <PERSON> Hefter </PERSON>, chief trial counsel for the lodging company based at Silver Spring, Md. `` There's absolutely no likelihood of confusion with <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>. The -LRB- McSleep -RRB- logo is very distinctive.'' The McSleep logo is a variation on the Quality Inns logo of a setting sun bordered by a black square, very distinct from McDonald's golden arch, said <PERSON> Hefter </PERSON>. <PERSON> Hefter </PERSON> said the `` Mc'' prefix was selected because it connotes a clear impression of value, affordable quality service. `` McDonald's may have played a part in promoting that type of image, but we believe that it has gone beyond that into the lexicon,'' he added McDonald's began its defense Monday in the trial which began July 18 before <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Niemeyer </PERSON>. <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bergold </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, vice president of advertising for <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, said the company spent more than $ 404 million last year in advertising. In one of more than a dozen videotaped McDonald's commercials presented in court Monday, the promotional character <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> McDonald </PERSON> taught children to put the prefix before many different words, including Mc-fries, Mc - -LRB- milk -RRB- shakes and Mc-best The purpose of the commercial was to create a Mc-language, specifically associated with <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Bergold </PERSON> said. `` McDonald's is the largest single-brand television advertiser in the country,'' he said. Surveys found that in the last four weeks, 89 percent of the nation's children between 2 and 7-years-old have visited a <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, and 96 percent of all adults have visited a McDonald's at least once, <PERSON> Bergold </PERSON> testified. `` We're trying to establish the impact and awareness that <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> has on the public, and why it's likely that they're going to be confused'' by the McSleep chain, said <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Kasander </PERSON>, an attorney for McDonald Chief trial counsel for McDonald's, former <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION> attorney general <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sachs </PERSON>, said a McDonald-sponsored survey indicated that more than 30 percent of the participants associated <PERSON> McSleep </PERSON> with <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>. McDonald's successfully sued the owner of a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> store called McBagel. A federal judge ruled that the business community generally recognizes that the `` Mc'' formative stands as a symbol of McDonald's services and products. But <PERSON> Hefter </PERSON> said other company names not associated with food bear the `` Mc'' prefix, including McThrifty and McLube. The McSleep Inns will offer a basic room with a bath, but no pool, meeting rooms, food service or restaurant. Quality Inn, a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Manor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Care </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, hopes to franchise about 200 such inns by 1991. Testimony in the trial is expected to end Wednesday.
