<DATELINE>NASHUA, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Fleet-Norstar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it has agreed to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Indian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Head </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banks </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a leading bank holding company in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION>, in an exchange of stock valued at $ 240 million. The deal, which is subject to approval by regulators and shareholders of Indian Head, calls for <PERSON> Fleet-Norstar </PERSON> to exchange 1.775 shares of its common stock for each of Indian Head's 4.7 million shares of common stock outstanding. The exchange ratio represents a price of about $ 44.37 -LCB- for each Indian Head share, based on <ORGANIZATION> Fleet-Norstar </ORGANIZATION>'s closing price of $ 25 a share on Friday, the companies said in a statement. The exchange of Indian Head convertible preferred stock into an equal number of Fleet-Norstar convertible preferred shares would boost the total value of the deal about $ 240 million, the banks stated. They said that price is approximately 1.7 times Indian Head's book value per common share and is a 30 percent premium over its market price, based on its close on Friday at $ 34.25 a share Indian Head Banks, based in <LOCATION> Nashua </LOCATION>, has assets of about $ 1.8 billion; <PERSON> Fleet-Norstar </PERSON>'s assets are about $ 25 billion. <PERSON> Fleet-Norstar </PERSON> has dual headquarters in <LOCATION> Providence </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> R.I. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Albany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION> Indian Head has 46 branches throughout <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> and earned $ 16.6 million in 1987, the company said. <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kiernan </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive of Fleet-Norstar, said the proposed acquisition would be `` a major step'' in expandin